      "title": "Proteomics analysis of fermentation broth under different nitrogen sources in Starmerella bombicola",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "S. bombicola was fermented under two different nitrogen sources (yeast extract or ammonium sulfate). The fermentation broth after 7 days\u2019 cultivation was taken for extracellular proteins analysis.",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "After the test product is reduced and alkylated, trypsin (mass ratio 1:50) is added, and it is enzymatically hydrolyzed at 37\u2103 for 20 hours. The enzymatic hydrolysis product was desalted and lyophilized, re-dissolved in 0.1% FA solution, and stored at -20\u2103 until use.",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "Solution A is an aqueous solution of 0.1% formic acid, solution B is an aqueous solution of 0.1% formic acid in acetonitrile (84% acetonitrile). After the chromatographic column is equilibrated with 95% A liquid, the sample is loaded onto the Trap column by the autosampler.",
